	<div class="blog-archive-entries-wrapper">
		<div id="unique-entry-id-264" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">We Wish You A Pirate Christmas</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Tuesday, 15 December 2009 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="jolly roger" src="jollyroger.jpg" width="40" height="39" /></div>I looked on You Tube for pirate christmas carol and found Rusty Cutlass playing We Wish You A Pirate Christmas.<br />See <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OiUH1oVdvwM" rel="external" title="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OiUH1oVdvwM">www.youtube.com/watch?v=OiUH1oVdvwM</a><br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-253" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Halloween</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Sunday, 01 November 2009 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="jolly roger" src="jollyroger.jpg" width="40" height="39" /></div>I hope you had the chance to dress up.<div class="image-right"><img class="imageStyle" alt="" src="page57_blog_entry253_2.jpg" width="67" height="100" /></div><br />You can probably guess what I dressed up as.  (Well without the wig).<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-249" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Prince Philip School</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Sunday, 18 October 2009 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="jolly roger" src="jollyroger.jpg" width="40" height="39" /></div>I have mentioned before that my son's school's nickname and logo is the 'pirates'.  So for talk like a pirate day the whole school even teachers (and the attached pre-school) dressed up as pirates.  It was really worth seeing and they did take a photo where they were being pirates (not the usual look at the camera and smile).  Sadly it looks as if will not be online.<br /><br />Also on the subject of the school, I would like to congratulate them, as next week the are celebrating their fiftieth birthday.  They are even in possession of a birthday letter from Prince Philip at Buckingham Palace.  Way to go guys keep up enjoying yourselves.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-242" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">International Talk Like A Pirate Day</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Saturday, 19 September 2009 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><a href="../../../pirate/phrases/phrases.html" rel="self" title="Phrases"><img class="imageStyle" alt="jolly roger" src="jollyroger.jpg" width="40" height="39" /></a></div>Ahoy there my hearties, it be talk like a pirate day today.  Is anyone else joining in?<br /><br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-241" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">International Talk Like A Pirate Day</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Thursday, 17 September 2009 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><a href="../../../pirate/phrases/phrases.html" rel="self" title="Phrases"><img class="imageStyle" alt="jolly roger" src="jollyroger.jpg" width="40" height="39" /></a></div>Although International Talk Like A Pirate Day is Saturday, several companies, schools etc are being pirates tomorrow.  So to help you here are some <a href="../../../pirate/phrases/phrases.html" rel="self" title="Phrases">phrases</a> that might help you be a pirate too.<br /><br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-239" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">International Talk Like A Pirate Day</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Monday, 14 September 2009 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><a href="../../../pirate/phrases/phrases.html" rel="self" title="Phrases"><img class="imageStyle" alt="jolly roger" src="jollyroger.jpg" width="40" height="39" /></a></div>Saturday 19th September is International Talk Like A Pirate Day (every year).  Please see <a href="http://talklikeapirate.com/about.html" rel="external" title="www.talklikeapirate.com">www.talklikeapirate.com</a>, <a href="http://www.wikihow.com/Talk-Like-a-Pirate" rel="external" title="www.wikihow.com/Talk-Like-a-Pirate">http://www.wikihow.com/Talk-Like-a-Pirate</a> and <a href="http://www.yarr.org.uk/talk/" rel="external" title="www.yarr.org.uk">www.yarr.org.uk/talk</a> for more information.  I have listed out some <a href="../../../pirate/phrases/phrases.html" rel="self" title="Phrases">phrases</a> that might help under our pirates section.  You are welcome to write a post for this blog in pirate talk, just send it via the squeak page.  Being land locked at the moment, my son has even found a song for us, go and read the <a href="../../../pirate/song/song.html" rel="self" title="Song Lyrics">Last Saskatchewan Pirate Lyrics</a>.  His <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4qtX2qy4wug" rel="external" title="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4qtX2qy4wug">school</a>'s nick name is the pirates and so are celebrating it on the Friday.<br /></div></div>
	</div>
	
	 

